subSubSection.paragraph:
56.
Theognete zapatista Anderson
, new species
( Figures 146 , 181 , 216 )

Diagnosis. Size. Length, male, 2.33–3.15mm ; female, 2.75–3.15mm . Width, male, 1.32–1.85mm ; female, 1.52–1.80mm . As for
T. schaubeli
except pronotum weakly cordate, with vestiture sparse, irregularly distributed except along glabrous middle area, suberect to erect, moderately long; flanks with distinct oblique sulci. Elytra with broad appressed to suberect scales linearly arranged along intervals, scales overlapping on at least some intervals. Aedeagus as in Fig. 181 .
Natural history . Collected from berlese extraction of oak-pine-liquidambar forest leaf litter at an elevation of 1500m and from tropical montane mixed forest at an elevation of 1000m .
Derivation of specific name . Noun in apposition; named after the revolutionary Zapatista Army of the Chiapan highlands.
